{"id":4174,"date":"2024-12-16T14:44:52","date_gmt":"2024-12-16T14:44:52","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=4174"},"modified":"2024-12-16T14:44:52","modified_gmt":"2024-12-16T14:44:52","slug":"rock-smash-items","status":"publish","type":"wiki","link":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/items\/rock-smash-items\/","title":{"rendered":"Rock Smash Items"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Rock Smash helps you break special rocks that block your path in the overworld. Occasionally, breaking rocks via Rock Smash can also reward you with different items and wild encounters. <\/p>\n<p>This page will detail all the items you can get from smashing breakable rocks, and it will detail a farming process to help you farm Rock Smash items faster.<\/p>\n<h2>All Rock Smash Items<\/h2>\n<table class=\"table grey center zebra even-2col bolded-1stcol\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Item<\/th>\n<th>Screenshot<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Blue Shard<\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/01-pokemon-unbound-blue-shard.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Green Shard<\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/02-pokemon-unbound-green-shard.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Red Shard<\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/03-pokemon-unbound-red-shard.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Yellow Shard<\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/04-pokemon-unbound-yellow-shard.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Everstone<\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/05-pokemon-unbound-everstone.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Hard Stone<\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/06-pokemon-unbound-hard-stone.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Heart Scale<\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/07-pokemon-unbound-heart-scale.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Stardust<\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/08-pokemon-unbound-stardust.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Revive<\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/09-pokemon-unbound-revive.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Old Amber<\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/10-pokemon-unbound-old-amber.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Armor Fossil<\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/11-pokemon-unbound-armor-fossil.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Root Fossil\t <\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/12-pokemon-unbound-root-fossil.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Skull Fossil<\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/13-pokemon-unbound-skull-fossil.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Helix Fossil<\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/14-pokemon-unbound-helix-fossil.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Sail Fossil\t <\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/15-pokemon-unbound-sail-fossil.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2>Farming Rock Smash Drops<\/h2>\n<p>An easy strategy to get Rock Smash items quickly is to repeatedly farm specific rocks found in the Great Desert, since they respawn if you move a bit off screen.<\/p>\n<p>To do this, you must first gain access to the Great Desert, which lies between Dehara City and Gurun Town. This area is unlocked after defeating Dehara City\u2019s Gym Leader &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/gyms\/dehara-city-gym\/\">Galavan<\/a> &#8211; and obtaining the <a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/items\/key-items\/#gogoggles\">Go-Goggles<\/a> from a nearby house.<\/p>\n<div class=\"callout-box\"><strong>Note:<\/strong> It is recommended to stock up on Super Repels or Max Repels to avoid wild Pokemon encounters while breaking rocks.<\/div>\n<p><strong>Step 1:<\/strong> Starting from the Dehara City Pokemon Center, go straight up the path and head towards the tunnel situated at the eastern end of the city. <\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/16-pokemon-unbound-dehara-citys-pokemon-center.jpg\" alt=\"Dehara City\u2019s Pokemon Center \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Dehara City\u2019s Pokemon Center<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 2:<\/strong> Go through the tunnel and come out the other side to reach the Great Desert. <\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/17-pokemon-unbound-reaching-the-great-desert.jpg\" alt=\"Reaching the Great Desert \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Reaching the Great Desert<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 3:<\/strong> Make your way into the desert until you see a cactus towards the bottom of your screen. <\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/18-pokemon-unbound-path-towards-cactus.jpg\" alt=\"Path towards cactus \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Path towards cactus<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 4:<\/strong> From here, take a few more steps and you\u2019ll come across another cactus next to a small pathway leading down to a new part of the desert.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/19-pokemon-unbound-path-leading-to-opening.jpg\" alt=\"Path leading to opening \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Path leading to opening<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 5:<\/strong> Go through the small opening here until you reach the end, and there\u2019s another cactus here. <\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/20-pokemon-unbound-path-leading-to-next-cactus.jpg\" alt=\"Path leading to next cactus \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Path leading to next cactus<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 6:<\/strong> Head towards the west from the cactus, and follow this west until you reach the end of the path.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/21-pokemon-unbound-path-leading-to-rocks.jpg\" alt=\"Path leading to rocks \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Path leading to rocks<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 7:<\/strong> Here you\u2019ll find a set of 3 boulders and 3 breakable rocks, which you can use to quickly farm Rock Smash items. <\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/22-pokemon-unbound-location-of-the-rocks-to-farm-for-items.jpg\" alt=\"Location of the rocks to farm for items \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Location of the rocks to farm for items<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 8:<\/strong> Use Rock Smash on the right-most rock so you can push the boulder in front of it. Then push this boulder towards the top, as far as you can.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/23-pokemon-unbound-pushing-the-boulder-towards-the-top.jpg\" alt=\"Pushing the boulder towards the top \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Pushing the boulder towards the top<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 9:<\/strong> The boulder will, on its own, stop being pushed once it reaches the skeleton at the end of the area. <\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/24-pokemon-unbound-placing-the-boulder-next-to-skeleton.jpg\" alt=\"Placing the boulder next to skeleton \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Placing the boulder next to skeleton<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 10:<\/strong> From here, go back down and the rock that you previously destroyed will have respawned. <\/p>\n<p>You can now break all 3 rocks to farm items, and if you want to push up the other 2 boulders you can, or you can just walk around them.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/25-pokemon-unbound-previously-broken-rock-respawned.jpg\" alt=\"Previously broken rock respawned \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Previously broken rock respawned<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 11:<\/strong> After breaking the 3 rocks, walk back up to the boulder near the top of the area. Once you reach this spot, the rocks at the bottom will have respawned again.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/26-pokemon-unbound-walking-back-to-the-boulder-pushed-to-the-top.jpg\" alt=\"Walking back to the boulder pushed to the top \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Walking back to the boulder pushed to the top<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 12:<\/strong> Keep running back and forth, and each time you repeat this process, the rocks will respawn and can be smashed again to obtain new items. <\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/27-pokemon-unbound-repeating-the-farming-process.jpg\" alt=\"Repeating the farming process \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Repeating the farming process<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>You can repeat this strategy to quickly farm as many Rock Smash items as you want. Using Max Repels while running back and forth will help you avoid wild Pokemon encounters from the rocks, which also speeds up this process.<\/p>\n\n        <a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/items\/\" class=\"parent-page-card\">\n            <picture class=\"card-img\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/07\/items-market.jpg\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/07\/items-market.jpg 200w, https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/07\/items-market-150x150.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" \/>\t\t\t\t            <\/picture>\n            <span class=\"card-info\">\n                <span class=\"card-info__caption\">Back to:<\/span>\n                <strong class=\"wiki-title\">Items<\/strong>\n            <\/span>\n        <\/a>\n\n\t\t\n","protected":false},"featured_media":4175,"parent":288,"menu_order":0,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false},"categories":[13],"class_list":["post-4174","wiki","type-wiki","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-items"],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki\/4174","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/wiki"}],"up":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki\/288"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/4175"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=4174"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=4174"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}